<subSubSection id="ACD00A39412E0F4B012949E2FD91CD10" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="ED15CC2AB1DE0C4FFDE6E27C0F9FC5A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="309112C619177B39400B85F49CA82631" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
In Yunnan, specimens were collected along sides of a rocky stream in a valley at night. 
<taxonomicName id="1EAD7713A8925D93D85C42B9D12EA010" authorityName="Orchymont" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Coelostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coelostoma coomani" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coomani">
<emphasis id="676FB37636C90C1EA986C4A450955212" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Coelostoma coomani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Orchymont, 1932 and 
<taxonomicName id="F76B958F53D5D2DE3974F2A2D718C7D1" class="Malacostraca" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. phallicum" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phallicum">
<emphasis id="8305F989B5D7E9983D3E97346D5EE8C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. phallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Orchymont, 1940 were also collected in the same habitat. Adult individuals attracted by light (
<bibRefCitation id="BE11A053B5E0FD68681ED2DD66674792" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" author="Jia, F-L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="354 - 376" refId="B13" refString="Jia, F-L, Aston, P, Fikacek, M, 2014. Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae). Zootaxa 3887 (3): 354 - 376, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" title="Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" volume="3887" year="2014">Jia et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Parameres slightly longer than median lobe, gradually broadened from base to middle, outer face not curved, apical third parallel-sided, apex narrower than apex of median lobe, truncate, rounded outwards and nearly rectangularly inwards.
</paragraph>
<caption id="48E3D28ABF9D7B8082029D27F89D6F0F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666191" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="CC82059C64BD0AC43800E22269381CF0" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="4A523649B93EA0A4EE1299F71D4C1627" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Figure 9.</emphasis>
Dorsal view of Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="47F02EE5F55571800426039CF48EFFFA" authorityName="Mouchamps" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Holocoelostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holocoelostoma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ECBF6AA31DF090AA0529E1AE1D39BC07" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Holocoelostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D091D2FC0DB970B58E14C8E3487419BC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BB430B7E1E5307A85CD23E9AC3B35ECC" authorityName="Pu" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Coelostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coelostoma sulcatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatum">
<emphasis id="A4727D4BBACBCF6DDE895ED0697A4FB8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Coelostoma sulcatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pu, 1963 
<emphasis id="D796638E5C11BC32F47AB795A6343951" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6B34A50A6CBC862C954D2863AD699BE1" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Coelostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coelostoma stultum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stultum">
<emphasis id="A3B08F8CD67A8AEA02EA681332566EE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Coelostoma stultum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Walker, 1858). Scale bar: 1.0 mm (
<emphasis id="9F242DED2AF583C2AD8327BBC9C49CD6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">A, B</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="802B6782DC08AE0F8DE75B63F889008C" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="ABAA8D8B2D17807C3846DD9CC2CCA65A" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A8FADD95B667F1CCB61C2D3E3CA50400" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
China (Guangxi, Jiangxi, Yunnan), Thailand (
<bibRefCitation id="5255F9E750C4B838FF0A4A4CC6673074" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" author="Jia, F-L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="354 - 376" refId="B13" refString="Jia, F-L, Aston, P, Fikacek, M, 2014. Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae). Zootaxa 3887 (3): 354 - 376, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" title="Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" volume="3887" year="2014">Jia et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7DA1FB45094DFF4C1BA2C0D4E3B6D051" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4232.1.8" author="Jia, F-L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="113 - 122" refId="B15" refString="Jia, F-L, Lin, R-C, Chan, E, Skale, A, Fikacek, M, 2017. Two new species of Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 from China and additional faunistic records of the genus from the Oriental Region (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae: Coelostomatini). Zootaxa 4232 (1): 113 - 122, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4232.1.8" title="Two new species of Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 from China and additional faunistic records of the genus from the Oriental Region (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae: Coelostomatini)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4232.1.8" volume="4232" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). New record for Yunnan.
</paragraph>
